> Hi Volks- Can anyone suggest a way to keep my radio settings when I
> disconnect the battery?  I disconnect my battery every time I work on my bus
> and I generally forget to reset the radio until I am on my way out of
> town..... Ted (financial report coming- fund drive was a great success)
> 
What you need is a disconect battery terminal.
<A HREF="http://www.vehicle-wiring-products.co.uk/VWPweb2000/BATTCON/BATTCON.html">http://www.vehicle-wiring-products.co.uk/VWPweb2000/BATTCON/BATTCON.html</A>
Scroll down to just above the quick release battery terminals.
You can also purchase a device that plugs into the cigarette lighter but as 
you posted this on vintage bus you may not have one fitted right? Mike  
